  "brief": "<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Market Overview</h2>\nMarkets are pushing higher across the board with small-caps leading the charge (IWM +2.16%), signaling risk-on appetite despite elevated VIX at 28. The Dow's outperformance (+1.63% vs SPY +0.99%) suggests value rotation is gaining momentum. Iran war headlines continue to dominate, but markets are shrugging off geopolitical noise for now.\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> What to Watch</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>ISM Manufacturing PMI (2:00 PM ET)</strong> - Key gauge of factory activity with multiple components releasing simultaneously</li>\n<li><strong>Oil rig count data (5:00 PM ET)</strong> - Critical given ongoing Iran supply concerns and rising crude prices</li>\n<li><strong>Iran war developments</strong> - Any escalation could spike energy prices and reverse risk-on sentiment</li>\n<li><strong>End-of-month flows</strong> - Institutional rebalancing could drive afternoon volatility</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-amber\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚡ Key Driver</div>Iran war creating classic flight-to-safety vs. risk-on tension. Oil prices rising but equities climbing anyway - this divergence won't last.</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Sector Rotation</h2>\nIndustrials (XLI +2.74%) and Utilities (XLU +2.56%) are leading, suggesting infrastructure/defensive plays are in favor. Tech lagging at just +0.25% signals money rotating out of growth into value and cyclicals. Healthcare's +2.21% pop adds to the defensive tone despite overall risk-on move.\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-green\"><div class=\"callout-label\">✦ Bull Case</div>Small-cap outperformance and declining VIX (-2.86%) suggest institutional buying underneath. Value rotation could have legs if economic data cooperates.</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-red\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚠ Bear Case</div>Tech weakness with VIX still near 28 screams fragile rally. Iran headlines could explode higher at any moment, crushing this risk-on move.</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Levels That Matter</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>SPY 720</strong> - Key resistance level that's held multiple times this month</li>\n<li><strong>QQQ 670</strong> - Must hold for tech to participate in any sustained rally</li>\n<li><strong>VIX 25</strong> - Break below signals genuine risk-off sentiment fading</li>\n<li><strong>IWM 280</strong> - Small-cap breakout level that could trigger broader value rotation</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr>\n<p><em>Not a prediction. A preparation. Make your plan before the bell.</em></p>"
